Fields Landing first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Fields Landing had a population of 287. The population density was {{convert|1,036.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Fields Landing was 192 (66.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (1.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 16 (5.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 7 (2.4%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 14 (4.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 55 (19.2%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 47 persons (16.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Fields Landing CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0624022 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 139 households, out of which 19 (13.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 40 (28.8%) were married-couple households, 15 (10.8%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 47 (33.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 37 (26.6%) had a male householder with no partner present. 57 households (41.0%) were one person, and 23 (16.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.06.<ref name=DP1/> There were 63 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (45.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Fields Landing CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0624022 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 60 people (20.9%) under the age of 18, 27 people (9.4%) aged 18 to 24, 87 people (30.3%) aged 25 to 44, 72 people (25.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 41 people (14.3%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 35.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 114.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 139 housing units at an average density of {{convert|501.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 139 (100.0%) were occupied. Of these, 75 (54.0%) were owner-occupied, and 64 (46.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

